  "raw_response": "```json\n{\n  \"title\": \"Crude Oil Hourly Entry Using Daily Propulsion Block Context\",\n  \"school\": \"ICT\",\n  \"asset\": \"CL1! (Crude Oil)\",\n  \"timeframe\": \"1H\",\n  \"market_context\": \"Crude oil is in a daily downtrend with a daily propulsion block already framing bearish bias. Dropping to the hourly chart to find a lower time frame entry aligned with the daily propulsion block context, with previous day highs lined up as inducement above price near 83.87.\",\n  \"key_observation\": \"Price rallies into the daily propulsion block area on the hourly chart, forming a series of up-close candles. A close below those up-close candles creates a bearish order block from which to short, targeting sell-side liquidity below.\",\n  \"analysis_steps\": [\n    \"Identify previous day highs lined up on the hourly chart as inducement/buy-side liquidity.\",\n    \"Mark the daily propulsion block as the higher time frame point of interest where a reaction is expected.\",\n    \"Wait for price to react off the propulsion block area and watch a series of up-close candles form.\",\n    \"Look for a candle to close below that series of up-close candles to form a bearish order block; the first candle that wicks below but does not close below is not counted.\",\n    \"Once a true close below the up-close candles occurs, take a short entry at the order block.\",\n    \"Place stop above the high of the order block/breaker block (analyst's personal preference).\",\n    \"Target sell-side liquidity at the prior low below.\"\n  ],\n  \"outcome\"",
